definitions.definition: The exchange or buying and selling of commodities ; especially the exchange of merchandise , on a large scale, between different places or communities; extended trade or traffic.
Social intercourse; the dealings of one person or class in society with another; familiarity.
An 18th-century French card game in which the cards are subject to exchange , barter , or trade .
